Package: tabfm
Title: R Interface to 'TabFM', a Zero-Shot Foundation Model for Tabular Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Matt", "O'Reilly", email = "fermoymatt@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A thin wrapper around the 'TabFM' 'Python' package from Google
    Research (<https://github.com/google-research/tabfm>). Provides zero-shot
    classification and regression on tabular data via in-context learning,
    with no feature engineering or hyperparameter tuning.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
URL: https://github.com/mattyoreilly/tabfm
BugReports: https://github.com/mattyoreilly/tabfm/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Imports:
    reticulate,
    stats
Suggests:
    callr,
    knitr,
    pkgload,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9) with the 'tabfm' package (see
    install_tabfm())
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
